# TypeScript pre-existing error baseline
#
# One error pattern per line (matched with grep -F, literal string).
# Lines starting with # are comments.
# Empty lines are ignored.
#
# Usage: when tsc reports errors that are pre-existing and not caused
# by your current changes, add a substring of the error line here.
# The typecheck-hook.sh script will filter these out and only surface
# NEW errors introduced by your edits.
#
# Example patterns:
# middleware.ts(5,1): error TS2304
# Cannot find name 'process'
# Property '[Internal]' is missing
